==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simultaneous
<hw>Si`mul*ta"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>simultim</ets> at the same time, fr. L. <ets>simul</ets>. See
<er>Simulate</er>.]</ety> <def>Existing, happening, or done, at the same
time; <as>as, <ex>simultaneous</ex> events</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Si`mul*ta"ne*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Si`mul*ta"ne*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Simultaneous equations</b></col> <fld>(Alg.)</fld>,
<cd>two or more equations in which the values of the unknown quantities
entering them are the same at the same time in both or in
all.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simulty</ent>⟦br⟧
